Class AbstractJavaModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.modelio.api.module.AbstractJavaModule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IModule

    public abstract class AbstractJavaModule
extends java.lang.Object
implements IModule
    Default implementation of the IModule interface.

    All Modelio java modules should inherit from this class.

    • Field Detail

      • imageRegistry

        protected ImageRegistry imageRegistry
        The module image registry.

        This registry contains the module stereotypes images and icons. This registry is disposed when the module is unloaded.

        Sub classes may use it to store other images as well.
        Sub classes should not set this property to another registry.

      • uninit

        public void uninit()
        Description copied from interface: IModule
        Method automatically called just before the disposal of the module.

        The uninit method allows the developer to execute the desired un-initialization code at this step. For example, if an IExpertise have been registered in the IModule.init() method, this method is the perfect place to remove them.

        This method should never be called by the developer because it is already invoked by the tool.

        Specified by:
        uninit in interface IModule
